        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 2:12PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saratoga Springs, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deans Corners, Cossayuna, Center Falls, Goose Island, Adamsville,
Grangerville, Northumberland, Middle Falls, Eddy Corners, Fitch
Point, Starks Knob, Clarks Mills, Saratoga Race Course, Saratoga
Springs, Burgoyne, Quaker Springs, Ketchums Corners, Greenwich, The
Saratoga Battllefield, and Thomson.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 14 and 15.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central New York...and southern Vermont.</instruction>
